{"type":"message","id":"7a868b75","parentId":"5579f86f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:06:35.336Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ya7rf6rhu15g_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 040551\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful single action I can take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n2. Key insight discovered: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - compression and causal discovery are the same problem\r\n3. Next action identified: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending actions include:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is a substantial experiment. Let me think about what concrete file edit I can make to advance this.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n2. Or create an experiment script that processes the pulse logs\r\n3. Or update the research document with the TIC approach\r\n\r\nGiven the \"ONE concrete action\" constraint and preference for file edits, I should:\r\n- Create the TIC experiment code/script\r\n- Or update the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY document with implementation details\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist. The last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-24 040325.md`. The pulse logs should be in `logs/` directory.\r\n\r\nI think the most impactful action would be to create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script for this since the pulse.ps1 is PowerShell-based.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions more carefully:\r\n- \"Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\" is also pending\r\n- \"Implement TIC classifier\" is the main next action\r\n\r\nI'll create a TIC experiment script that processes the pulse logs. Let me write a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n\r\n\r\n2. Performs basic pattern analysis to distinguish stable elements from transient variations\r\n3. Establishes a foundational classification mechanism for testing invariance detection\r\n\r\nI'll develop a minimal viable approach to demonstrate the core concept, focusing on extracting structural consistency across pulse executions.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant patterns from variant content across pulse logs, then measure its accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Loads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts candidate invariant markers (file paths, repeated phrases, goal references)\r\n3. Classifies content as invariant/variant\r\n4. Tests next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n5. Outputs metrics against success criteria\r\n\r\nThis advances Phase 1 by operationalizing the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$LogCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPath = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Success criteria: >70% classification, >60% prediction`n\"\r\n\r\n# Collect pulse logs\r\n$logs = Get-ChildItem \"$LogPath/pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $LogCount\r\n\r\nif ($logs.Count -lt 2) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 2 pulse logs for TIC experiment\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($logs.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content from each log\r\n$pulseData = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $logs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulseData += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        Name = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Lines = ($content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Invariant Detection Heuristics ---\r\n# Invariant patterns: file paths, goal references, phase markers, key terms\r\n$invariantPatterns = @(\r\n    '\\b(Phase \\d|Phase \\d COMPLETE)\\b',\r\n    '\\b(Active|Pending|Completed)\\b',\r\n    '\\b(research/|logs/|state/|scripts/)[^\\s]+\\.md',\r\n    '\\b(Achieved|Success|NEXT ACTION|Pending)\\b',\r\n    '\\b\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}\\b',\r\n    '\\b(Breakaway|TemporalAttention|Infant|Compositional)\\b'\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Variant patterns: timestamps, specific values, line counts, ephemeral details\r\n$variantPatterns = @(\r\n    '\\b\\d{6}\\.md\\b',\r\n    'Last updated:',\r\n    'Last pulse:',\r\n    'Line \\d+',\r\n    'pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}'\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Analyze each pulse for invariant/variant content\r\n$classificationResults = @()\r\n$invariantHits = 0\r\n$variantHits = 0\r\n$totalSegments = 0\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulseData) {\r\n    $lines = $pulse.Content -split \"`n\"\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ([string]::IsNullOrWhiteSpace($line)) { continue }\r\n        $totalSegments++\r\n        \r\n        $\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:06:23\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339595335}}
{"type":"message","id":"30bd29b1","parentId":"7a868b75","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:06:46.718Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse ran and produced a mutation proposal for `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1`. Let me summarize this for Zach.","thinkingSignature":"c110bf365888fdcab9c1adc140d105303075d7fdd25af2b37b968fdf4d8b35fb"},{"type":"text","text":"## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 04:05 AM\n\n**Observation:** The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the **COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY** hypothesis — the idea that causal structure and invariant structure are the same thing.\n\n**Proposed Mutation:** Create `experiments/tic_classifier.ps1` — a classifier that:\n- Loads the last 20 pulse logs\n- Extracts invariant markers (file paths, goal references, phase markers, key terms like \"Breakaway\", \"TemporalAttention\", \"Infant\")\n- Classifies content as invariant vs. variant\n- Tests next-pulse prediction accuracy\n- Validates against success criteria: **>70% classification accuracy, >60% prediction accuracy**\n\nThis is Phase 1 operationalization — turning the architecture insight into an empirical test. No mutations were applied this cycle (1 proposal pending)."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1994,"output":218,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14166,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774339595337}}
